Ticket Update XXVI v.3.9.0.r900
Bug Fixes

    Fixed a bug relating to the admin section not showing any options other than user edit
    Fixed a bug that was causing the title title text to use the wrong font
    Fixed the bookmark button. It was not displaying properly
    Fixed the button size issue, this was a result of some reset CSS code and me not taking into account this.
    Tickets was not working very well at all with some small screen devices (Smart Phones) and this has been mostly resolved. This is something that will forever be tweeked as new features get added and the layout improves


New Features

    Working on making tickets fit with the new website colors and feel. When the new website launches tickets should already feel right at home
    Tickets is now using a new font based icon system.
        It will help tickets load faster
        The changes also make generating new icon themes easier
    The top menu only shows categories which you have tickets in, if you do not have a ticket in by me it will not show up for you.
    The tabs have been reworked to flow better with the layout.


Known Issues

    Searching By project does not work
    Page indicators in a search result do not currently work.
    There are some issues with editing that have been around since editing was in place. All of the ticket code links are not working as intended with the new editing system.
    Commenting on a ticket that was closed or reopened will generate extra replies.
    Search is currently missing from the layout. I am working on a location to put it so that it fits



