Tickets Hotfix v.3.5.2.r700
Bug Fixes

    Fixed the [url=http://www.google.com] not translating to the correct URL bug. It should be working properly now.


New Features

    If tickets is behaving strangly or you are just not getting the result you are looking for now you can "reset tickets". Simply load up your user page by clicking on your name in the top right corner and then click reset tickets.
    Importants of a ticket is now shown in a graphical display on the ticket list. This enables for faster and easier view of what is the most important ticket.
    Ticket lists now show when a ticket was created.
    Entering a url into a ticket or response in the form of http://www.google.com will no be converted to a link


Known Issues

    Searching By project does not work
    Page indicators in a search result do not currently work.
    There are some issues with editing that have been around since editing was in place. All of the ticket code links are not working as intended with the new editing system.
    Commenting on a ticket that was closed or reopened will generate extra replies.



Live Ticket Update XXIII v.3.5.0.r582
Bug Fixes

    Clicking on the "No User (Please Login) link correctly takes you to the login window. (Finally)
    Trying to take an action on a ticket when you are not logged in will now force you to login. Before events were seeming to happen when a person was not logged in, but where blocked by the server and not shown to the user. This lead to confusion.
    Fixed a TON of bugs related to the login process.
    You can once again change your email address by clicking on your name
    Fixed the posting 4 replies bug


New Features

    New Ticket layout. Tickets has separated from the website and is once again a separate product. Some of the same feel is in the new look, but much is new.
        Tickets has become more HTML 5 friendly. Future updates where made to the styles to improve load times.
        New Layout is more friendly with any width of screen/window. All of the navagation is done in the header of the page.
        You can now see up to 30 tickets per screen instead of the normal 20.
        The body of a ticket now shows up as the first reply
        Tickets works much better on Smart phones. You can now check and interact will all of the ticket features straight from your phone. There may be bugs in how it work in the initial release, and it will be improved over time.
    You can login to tickets with a Google account. More OpenID providers will be enabled in the future, but for now its just google.
    Searching works. It is now a keyword search that searches the title, body, and id of the ticket.


Known Issues

    Searching By project does not work
    Page indicators in a search result do not currently work.
    There are some issues with editing that have been around since editing was in place. All of the ticket code links are not working as intended with the new editing system.
    Commenting on a ticket that was closed or reopened will generate extra replies.



