Live Ticket Update XX v.3.0.0.r301
Bug Fixes

    Fixed OpendDNS Server 2/PING is WARNING.
    Fixed RECOVERY Host Alert: RPCirc is UP.
    Fixed Main Internet Router/PING is OK.
    Fixed The Internet/PING is OK.
    Fixed OpendDNS Server 2/PING is WARNING.
    Fixed a javascript uncaught TypeError bug that would happen when there were no responses on a ticket.


New Features

    New tickets and new bugs are now closer linked to the areas they are for. The menu bar is going to be for global adjustments not just for links.
    Launch of mobile tickets
        This is basically a media query based shiv to make tickets work better on a smaller screen.
        This will also work on a desktop, just resize your browser window down and see the results.
    Editing is totally revamped.
        Tickets is now using the markitup editor that the main site is using This will be included at a later date.
        Tickets are now edited in line. When the modify button is clicked the editing interface will show up. Click save to make the changes, or cancel to undo any adjustments that were made.
    Recent Tickets has been removed from this version of tickets. Its going to be handled differently than before.
    Implemented Main Internet Router/PING is WARNING.
    Tickets are now sorted by priority then due date
    Bookmarks are now done in line vs though a toolbar button. You can click the (
    /
    ) icon anywhere it is on the page, and it will toggle the book mark for the ticket you have selected.


Known Issues

    Searching By project does not work
    Going directly to the user Page in Firefox can result in odd placement of the yes/no selector. This is a result of how Firefox renders report @font-face fonts.
    There are no page numbers, nor any way to show more then the default amount of tickets in the list view.
    Going directly to a ticketlist search result can lead to a broken page.
    There are some issues with editing that have been around since editing was in place. All of the ticket code links are not working as intended with the new editing system.
    Closed tickets are not showing up for some people. Even though a number shows up next to Closed Tickets.
    New tickets / bugs and new replies are not in their final form. These will be integrated into the new look in a later version.



Live Ticket Update XIX v.2.14.21.r217
Bug Fixes

    Large Graphs are finally working properly again. Not all of the graphs are back in place.
    All ticket lists, and responses should now display in the same order on all browsers
    Departments dropdown no longer looks cluttered. This was introduced with the last update. This has been solved by moving the adjustments to a new user page.
    Ticket email was showing too much information thus making looking at tickets less important. This has been fixed
    Fixed a bookmark bug that was introduced with ticket update XVIII



New Features

    User Pages are in place.
        This is a very early version. More features to this page will be added with time.
        The prime goal of user pages is to allow other people to see basic stats on tickets, based on the user they have selected.
        User pages will eventually take user name,user id, as well as real name as a parameter. Currently they only support user id.
        User pages are the first location of the new graphs.
    Bugs are now separated out into their own area. No longer will bugs show up in the ticket list.



Known Issues

    Large Graphs are still not working properly
    Searching By project does not work
    Some themes do not work 100%
    Going directly to the user Page in Firefox can result in odd placement of the yes/no selector. This is a result of how Firefox renders report @font-face fonts.
    There are no page numbers, nor any way to show more then the default amount of tickets in the list view.
    Problem or bug icons do not show up in the ticket list. No longer relative
    Going directly to a ticketlist search result can lead to a broken page.



Live Ticket Update XVIII v.2.12.16.r175
Bug Fixes

    Fixed a bug that was causing tickets to show the wrong replies.
    Fixed many bugs relating to the theme generator.
    Making a new ticket will once again take you to the ticket you just created
    Notice text was too hard to read as a result of this update. This has been fixed.



New Features

    Tickets now uses localStorage. If your browser supports it tickets that you have recently viewed will load up much faster.
    Bug reports are now separated out into their own section. This will make it easier to file a bug report and see the progress associated with it.
        Bug reports do not have a due date, nor do they have a department. Bug reports will have a Priority level and a product. They will look a lot like a ticket, but will be missing some of the components that are not needed in a bug report.
        This is just a framework release. The bug tickets are not out yet, and the button does not currently do anything.
    All of the notifications now have their own icon. The icons are more descriptive of what the notification is actually telling you.
    Along with the new notification icons comes new icons for tickets. Tickets should look more like the website again.



Known Issues

    Large Graphs are still not working properly
    Some themes do not work 100%
    There are no page numbers, nor any way to show more then the default amount of tickets in the list view.
    Problem or bug icons do not show up in the ticket list.
    Going directly to a ticketlist search result can lead to a broken page.



Live Ticket Update XVII v.2.8.13.r161
Bug Fixes
1. The Update notes page was using the old theme. This has been fixed.
2. Fixed a bug that was causing bookmarked checks to apear on replies.

New Features
1. Navagation has been made dramatically easier, and more to the point. All tickets are selected though the ticket list. This will reducde the amount of CSS needed, as well as allow for the reduction in a lot of the javascript as well.
2. Look and feak of tickets has changed. No longer are the areas separated from their headers.
3. CSS3 has attacked tickets. There are now lots of cool new CSS3 tags running rampant around tickets. If you see square corners and no drop shadows you are using an old browser.
4. there is now an [ img ] tag. it allows for linking to offsite images within tickets. No matter what size it is, it will work.

Known Issues
1. Large Graphs are still not working properly
2. Some themes do not work 100%
3. There are no page numbers, nor any way to show more then the default amount of tickets in the list view.
4. Problem or bug icons do not show up in the ticket list.

